          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "An opaque cookie. If you pass this cookie to "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/security/1395676-sectrustsetexceptions"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", that function sets a list of exceptions for future processing of the certificate. Once this list of exceptions are set, a subsequent call to "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/security/2980705-sectrustevaluatewitherror"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " for that certificate will return "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "true"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "inlineHead",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Note: "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "If a new error occurs that did not occur when this function was called originally, the subsequent call to "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/security/2980705-sectrustevaluatewitherror"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " can still fail. For example, if the certificate expires between calling "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "SecTrustCopyExceptions"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " and "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/security/2980705-sectrustevaluatewitherror"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", evaluation will fail."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Normally this API should only be called after asking the user how to proceed, and even then, only if the user explicitly tells your application to trust the current certificate chain in spite of the errors presented."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
